-the losses due to secondary reactions in the

. Position-sensitive plastic scintillators and
the multi-wire detectors.
The total uncertainty of the cross section
results from the combined uncertainty on each
correction factor. The total uncertainty of the cross
sections is lower than 15% from mercury down to
dysprosium isotopes. For lighter products, due to the
increasing contribution of multiple reaction in the
target and secondary reactions in the target windows,
uncertainty amounts to 20% from terbium to europium,
and is of the order of 30% for the lightest fragments
between samarium and neodymium. The uncertainty of the
cross sections resulting from the statistics of the
measurement and from the precision in the
identification is limited to about the half of the
total combined uncertainty of the different correction
factors.
The SIS accelerator of GSI.
A 1 cm thick liquid-hydrogen target was inserted at the
bottom of a helium cryostat between thin titanium foils
of 36 mg/cm**2 thickness. A thin niobium foil of
60 mg/cm**2 was placed behind the target to increase
the rate of bare ions. The number of hydrogen atoms per
unit area in the beam line was 60 time larger than the
number of titanium and niobium atoms.  As the
geometrica cross section of gold reaction is about 3
